						<div class="postbody">What something does versus how it achieves it. The former is important prior to mentally assimilating the latter, sometimes at increasing levels of detail. It's like trying to understand source code without a clear idea of the overall architecture. That's what I understand you to be saying, and maybe the links answer some of it. It wouldn't surprise me of they don't, as once one has an overview, one doesn't forget so doesn't need to document, while the details are easily forgotten and written down.</div>

