				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">mrhyde wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">So I will interpret this as: one toggle in PPUCTRL0 selects one of the pattern tables as active; only tiles from one of this pattern table can be displayed the same time. Right?</div><br />Correct. At any time, the background uses one bank (tiles 0-255 at $0000 or tiles 256-511 at $1000) depending on that flag. Depending on other bits written to the same port, sprites can use the same bank, use the other bank, or use 8x16 pixel sprites from both banks.</div>

